parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front end wobble/steering instability can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when decelerating or turning at speeds between 25-55 mph.
symptoms: The front end of the motorcycle wobbles or shakes violently
or when the rider takes their hands off the handlebars or grips them lightly. The wobble can be severe enough to cause the rider to lose control of the motorcycle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the starter magnet can cause the starter to short out, leading to electrical system damage, and potentially causing a fire hazard.
The failure of the ignition system can cause the motorcycle to stall without warning, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
The failure of the headlight and starter switch can cause the headlight to turn off while driving, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: and needing to jiggle the starter switch to turn on the headlight.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inaccuracy of the speedometer can cause the rider to unknowingly exceed speed limits, leading to potential accidents and traffic violations.
symptoms: Speedometer reading lower than actual speed
discrepancy between speedometer reading and actual speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaking from the petcock can create a safety hazard, increasing the risk of fire or explosion, which can cause serious injury or death.
symptoms: fuel leaking onto the lower muffler.
